# Process Flow SVG Template

## Overview

Template for sequential information: workflows, how-it-works diagrams, pipelines, and step-by-step processes. Supports horizontal (left-to-right) and vertical (top-to-bottom) layouts.

---

## Base Structure

```svg
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1200 800" role="img">
  <title>[Process Name]</title>
  <desc>[Plain-text description: a N-step process showing how to...]</desc>

  <style>
    :root {
      --accent: #E94560;
      --secondary: #16213E;
      --bg: #FFFFFF;
      --text: #333333;
      --muted: #888888;
      --light-bg: #F8F9FA;
      --font: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    }

    text { font-family: var(--font); }
    .title { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; fill: var(--secondary); }
    .subtitle { font-size: 16px; fill: var(--muted); }
    .step-number { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; fill: white; }
    .step-title { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; fill: var(--text); }
    .step-desc { font-size: 13px; fill: var(--muted); }
    .source { font-size: 11px; fill: var(--muted); }
  </style>

  <rect width="1200" height="800" fill="var(--bg)" />

  <!-- Title -->
  <text x="600" y="50" class="title" text-anchor="middle">[Process Title]</text>
  <text x="600" y="78" class="subtitle" text-anchor="middle">[Brief context]</text>

  <!-- Process steps go here -->

  <!-- Brand Logo -->
  <g transform="translate(1100, 740)" opacity="0.5">
    <!-- logo-mark SVG contents -->
  </g>
</svg>
```

---

## Horizontal Flow (3-5 Steps)

Best for processes with 3-5 steps that fit on one row.

```svg
<!-- Step 1 -->
<g transform="translate(100, 250)">
  <!-- Step circle with number -->
  <circle cx="100" cy="0" r="28" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="100" y="7" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">1</text>

  <!-- Step card -->
  <rect x="20" y="45" width="160" height="120" rx="8" fill="var(--light-bg)" />
  <text x="100" y="80" class="step-title" text-anchor="middle">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="100" y="105" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Line 1 of description]</text>
  <text x="100" y="122" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Line 2 of description]</text>
</g>

<!-- Arrow 1→2 -->
<line x1="280" y1="250" x2="340" y2="250" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2"
      marker-end="url(#arrowhead)" />

<!-- Step 2 -->
<g transform="translate(340, 250)">
  <circle cx="100" cy="0" r="28" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="100" y="7" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">2</text>
  <rect x="20" y="45" width="160" height="120" rx="8" fill="var(--light-bg)" />
  <text x="100" y="80" class="step-title" text-anchor="middle">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="100" y="105" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Description]</text>
</g>

<!-- Arrow 2→3 -->
<line x1="520" y1="250" x2="580" y2="250" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2"
      marker-end="url(#arrowhead)" />

<!-- Step 3 -->
<g transform="translate(580, 250)">
  <circle cx="100" cy="0" r="28" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="100" y="7" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">3</text>
  <rect x="20" y="45" width="160" height="120" rx="8" fill="var(--light-bg)" />
  <text x="100" y="80" class="step-title" text-anchor="middle">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="100" y="105" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Description]</text>
</g>

<!-- Arrowhead marker definition -->
<defs>
  <marker id="arrowhead" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7" refX="10" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
    <polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="var(--accent)" />
  </marker>
</defs>
```

---

## Vertical Flow (5-8 Steps)

Best for longer processes or when step descriptions are detailed.

```svg
<!-- Step 1 -->
<g transform="translate(200, 120)">
  <!-- Number badge -->
  <circle cx="0" cy="25" r="22" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="0" y="32" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">1</text>

  <!-- Content -->
  <text x="45" y="18" class="step-title">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="45" y="40" class="step-desc">[Description of what happens in this step]</text>
</g>

<!-- Connector line -->
<line x1="200" y1="167" x2="200" y2="210" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2"
      stroke-dasharray="4,4" />

<!-- Step 2 -->
<g transform="translate(200, 210)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="25" r="22" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="0" y="32" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">2</text>
  <text x="45" y="18" class="step-title">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="45" y="40" class="step-desc">[Description]</text>
</g>

<!-- Continue pattern for each step, incrementing y by ~90 -->
```

---

## Alternating (Zigzag) Flow

For processes where you want visual variety. Steps alternate left and right.

```svg
<!-- Step 1 (left-aligned) -->
<g transform="translate(100, 150)">
  <circle cx="30" cy="30" r="24" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="30" y="37" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">1</text>
  <rect x="70" y="5" width="400" height="60" rx="8" fill="var(--light-bg)" />
  <text x="90" y="30" class="step-title">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="90" y="50" class="step-desc">[Description]</text>
</g>

<!-- Connector -->
<path d="M 500,200 Q 600,230 700,200" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="2"
      fill="none" stroke-dasharray="4,4" />

<!-- Step 2 (right-aligned) -->
<g transform="translate(630, 250)">
  <rect x="0" y="5" width="400" height="60" rx="8" fill="var(--light-bg)" />
  <text x="20" y="30" class="step-title">[Step Title]</text>
  <text x="20" y="50" class="step-desc">[Description]</text>
  <circle cx="430" cy="30" r="24" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="430" y="37" class="step-number" text-anchor="middle">2</text>
</g>
```

