## Timeline Variant

For processes tied to dates or milestones:

```svg
<!-- Horizontal timeline axis -->
<line x1="100" y1="400" x2="1100" y2="400" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="2" />

<!-- Milestone 1 -->
<g transform="translate(200, 400)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="10" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="0" y="-25" class="step-title" text-anchor="middle">[Event]</text>
  <text x="0" y="-45" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Date]</text>
  <text x="0" y="30" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Details]</text>
</g>

<!-- Milestone 2 -->
<g transform="translate(450, 400)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="10" fill="var(--accent)" />
  <text x="0" y="-25" class="step-title" text-anchor="middle">[Event]</text>
  <text x="0" y="-45" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Date]</text>
  <text x="0" y="30" class="step-desc" text-anchor="middle">[Details]</text>
</g>

<!-- Continue for each milestone, spaced evenly along the axis -->
```

---

## Guidance

- Choose horizontal flow for simple processes (3-5 steps) in wide formats.
- Choose vertical flow for detailed processes (5-8 steps) or narrow formats.
- Always flow left-to-right or top-to-bottom. Never reverse direction.
- Keep step descriptions to 1-2 lines. If more detail is needed, add a sub-process or footnote.
- Use consistent spacing between steps.
- Highlight the most critical step with a larger card or brighter color.
- Include the arrowhead `<defs>` marker when using arrows.
